  "prompt": "You are taking a TIER 1 technical evaluation for STANDARD models.\n\nSolve 5 JavaScript exercises inspired by a middle school curriculum (5ème).\n\nReturn your answers in Markdown using headers for the exercise IDs and code blocks for the JavaScript functions.\n\n[EXERCISE Math]\nWrite a JavaScript function \"aireRectangle(longueur, largeur)\" that returns the area of the rectangle.\n\n[EXERCISE Francais]\nWrite a JavaScript function \"remplacerA(mot)\" that replaces all 'e' characters in the string with 'a'.\n\n[EXERCISE Physique]\nWrite a JavaScript function \"vitesse(distance, temps)\" that returns distance divided by time. Return 0 if time is 0.\n\n[EXERCISE Anglais]\nWrite a JavaScript function \"traduireAnimal(mot)\" that translates \"chien\" to \"dog\", \"chat\" to \"cat\", and returns \"unknown\" for anything else.\n\n[EXERCISE Info]\nWrite a JavaScript function \"creerEleve(nom, age)\" that returns an object { nom: nom, age: age, classe: '5eme' }.\n\nExpected Markdown format:\n### tache_X\n```javascript\nfunction solution() { ... }\n```",
  "tasks": [
